      m_Calls: []
  m_text: In Singapore, there are several varieties of laksa, a spicy noodle soup
    made with coconut milk, ranging from the curry-like Sarawak laksa to the tamarind-tang
    of Penang laksa. However, none is more well-known than our native Katong laksa.
    The Katong locals, known as Peranakans*, are the source of inspiration for Katong
    laksa. It has a fiery sunset-colored, spicy soup stock that is flavored with
    coconut milk and dried shrimp. Cockles, prawns, and fishcake are added to the
    top.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
