      m_Calls: []
  m_text: Biryani is a flavorful and aromatic rice dish that originated in South
    Asia, specifically on the Indian subcontinent. Basmati rice, meat (such as chicken,
    mutton, or beef), and a flavorful mixture of spices are combined to make this
    one-pot meal. The specialty of biryani is its special cooking technique, which
    involves layering and slowly simmering partially cooked rice with meat to let
    the rice absorb the flavors of the meat and spices. As a reflection of the many
    cultural influences present in Singapore, biryani is a prominent feature of the
    country's culinary scene. Asian ingredients are blended together to create Singaporean
    cuisine, where biryani is a popular dish that is liked by both locals and tourists.
    According to the Straits Times, M Abdul, an Indian native from Tamil Nadu, is
    credited with bringing nasi biryani to Singapore.
