  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: Fish head curry is unique to Singapore, the epitome of a cultural melting
    pot. It mixes the spices of a typical South Indian curry with the fish head.
    Every ethnic group in Singapore has a unique curry dish that varies slightly
    from the others. Some people add coconut milk for a creamier texture, while others
    blend in tamarind paste for a hint of sourness. In the 1940s, the chef of a tiny
    Indian eatery invented fish head curry. Although fish head isn't traditionally
    associated with India, restaurant owner M.J. Gomez, who hails from Kerala in
    Southern India, combined the popular Chinese dish with Indian curry to win over
    his Chinese customers
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
