      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Fried Kway Teow also known as \u2018char kway teow\u2019 in Singapore,
    this indulgent wok-fried noodle dish has been a popular Singaporean hawker staple
    for decades. The origins of this dish of wok-fried noodles are in Teochew culture.
    The culture is native to the Guangdong province of China, specifically the Chaozhou
    region. The ingredients for char kway teow consist of a mixture of yellow wheat
    and flat rice noodles that are stir-fried with garlic, chili, lup cheong (a Chinese
    waxed sausage), eggs, fishcakes, and bean sprouts over high heat."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
